          <div class="e-content p-name comment-content">Micropub^1 is a <a class="h-cassis-username" href="https://twitter.com/W3C">@W3C</a> Candidate Recommendation!<a href="https://aaronparecki.com/2016/08/23/2/micropub-cr">https://aaronparecki.com/2016/08/23/2/micropub-cr</a>(replaces AtomPub^2 &amp; MetaWeblog^3)Congrats editor <a class="h-cassis-username" href="https://twitter.com/aaronpk">@aaronpk</a>, and <a class="h-cassis-username" href="https://twitter.com/socialwg">@socialwg</a>!^1 <a href="https://www.w3.org/TR/2016/CR-micropub-20160816/">https://www.w3.org/TR/2016/CR-micropub-20160816/</a>^2 <a href="https://tools.ietf.org/html/rfc5023">https://tools.ietf.org/html/rfc5023</a>^3 <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/MetaWeblog">https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/MetaWeblog</a>Great work <a class="h-cassis-username" href="https://twitter.com/aaronpk">@aaronpk</a> with brainstorming publicly, selfdogfooding, incubating in <a href="http://indieweb.org">indieweb.org</a>, proposing <a class="h-cassis-username" href="https://twitter.com/W3C">@W3C</a> Social Web Working Group, and patiently working through issues raised, iteratively improving the draft accordingly, all the while helping grow the number of deployed and live interoperable implementations!</div>
